                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7303</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-05T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Urgent. Reported troops have been ordered away from Los Mochis and that entire
                    population leaving with them. American settlers there fear another raid by
                    Indians. Request appropriate authorities to maintain adequate garrison
                    permanently at Los Mochis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
